<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-12T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5508: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-12T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 12,
                                        1924—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>154. Your 227, September 10, 5 p.m. You may orally communicate to Baron
                            Shidehara the essential portion of the first paragraph <pb facs="0488" n="374" xml:id="pg_374"/> of the Department’s 151, September 10, 4
                            p.m., down to and including “developments in China.”</p>
                        <p>You may repeat to Peking for its information the above mentioned first
                            paragraph of the Department’s 151.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>